Highlights
src/ → all core logic for analysis, visualization, and OpenAI integration

ui/ → Streamlit or Flask UI pages (modular)

data/sample_datasets/ → example datasets for demo/testing

assets/ → branding, CSS customization, logo, etc.

tests/ → unit tests for functions (can use pytest)

docs/ → for documenting how to use or contribute to the app

🛠️ Key Files Explained
File	Purpose
requirements.txt	All Python dependencies (e.g., pandas, streamlit, openai, statsmodels, etc.)
app.py	Main entry point to run the app
LICENSE	Choose MIT for open monetization freedom
README.md	High-level overview, features, how to run the app
settings.py	Store your OpenAI API key, config flags (load with .env later)

